Subject: [Bioc-devel] Important Bioconductor Release Deadlines
Message-ID: <BL1PR12MB53016CD3ECBB71FEE4DC7FF1F9602@BL1PR12MB5301.namprd12.prod.outlook.com>

The final day to submit packages to the contribution tracker to attempt to be included in the Bioconductor 3.20 release is Friday September 20th.  Submission by this date does not guarantee inclusion, the package must still undergo an official review and be accepted by October 23rd.

Please remember,  The Bioconductor 3.19 branch will be frozen Tuesday October 15th.   After that date, no changes will be permitted ever on that branch.

The deadline for devel Bioconductor 3.20 for packages to pass R CMD build and R CMD check is October 25th.  While you will still be able to make commits past this date,  This ensures any changes pushed to git.bioconductor.org are reflected in at least one build report before the devel branch will be copied to a release 3.20 branch.

Cheers,


